AmaMpondo king Zanozuko Tyelovuyo Sigcau has died. The kingdom released a statement late on Tuesday evening announcing his passing. His distraught mother, Nkosikazi Nobandla Sigcau, told the Dispatch in a report published on Wednesday that her 47-year-old son had been hospitalised since March. He was admitted at St Augustine Hospital in Durban and died on his way to Johannesburg to the Wits Donald Gordon Medical for liver treatment. This is a developing story. DispatchLIVE